    <!-- Project Surfboard Case Study Section -->
    <section id="project-surfboard" class="background-section">
        <div class="section-content">
            <h1 class="section-header">Project Surfboard</h1>
            
            <div class="section">
                <h2>Project Overview</h2>
                <p><strong>Project Surfboard</strong> was a bold and creative initiative aimed at securing sponsorship from the renowned surf brand Billabong. The project initially involved a seven-day challenge where I designed a custom surfboard and personally delivered it to Billabongâ€™s headquarters in Australia. Following this, I made a second attempt to connect with the brand by designing a hoodie and delivering a miniature surfboard to their Huntington Beach HQ.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h2>Purpose and Impact</h2>
                <p>The project sought to raise awareness about stroke rehabilitation and inspire others to take bold actions for meaningful causes. During the initial seven-day challenge, I pushed myself out of my comfort zone by participating in various discomfort activities, including stand-up comedy, singing on the street, and handing letters of kindness to strangers. Through these challenges, I raised over $400 for the Stroke Foundation, which supports stroke survivors with services like speech therapy, physiotherapy, and occupational therapy. <strong>Project Surfboard</strong> demonstrated the power of creativity and personal storytelling in creating connections and promoting social impact.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h2>Key Achievements</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Custom Designs:</strong> Created and delivered a custom surfboard and, in a later effort, a hoodie and tiny surfboard to pitch to Billabong.</li>
                    <li><strong>Fundraising for Stroke Support:</strong> Raised over $400 through a seven-day discomfort challenge for the Stroke Foundation.</li>
                    <li><strong>Awareness Campaign:</strong> Engaged a broader audience through social media, promoting stroke rehabilitation and sharing the journey.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

